headline: Defense Stocks Northrop Grumman and RTX Are Tanking. Is Lockheed Martin a Better Buy for Passive Income?
summary: Meanwhile, Lockheed reaffirmed its full-year outlook -- a noticeable reprieve after it fell 9.2% in a single session following its January report.  Lockheed Martin has a diversified business spanning four segments -- Aeronautics (led by its F-35 fighter jet program), Missiles and Fire Control, Rotary and Mission Systems, and Space.  This makes Lockheed fairly recession-proof, as the company is primarily focused on fulfilling orders and developing new projects, rather than trying to navigate business cycles.
